front_matter:
  id: pm-8d71
  title: "M5 follow-up: isolate override and renderer contexts"
  description: Prevent extension command overrides and renderer overrides from mutating caller result objects during failure and fallback flows.
  type: Task
  status: closed
  priority: 1
  tags[7]: "area:extensions",code,docs,"milestone:5",pm-cli,"priority:1",tests
  created_at: "2026-03-04T19:58:35.984Z"
  updated_at: "2026-03-04T20:13:14.026Z"
  deadline: "2026-03-06T19:58:20.000Z"
  author: cursor-maintainer
  estimated_minutes: 90
  acceptance_criteria: "runCommandOverride and runRendererOverride use isolated context snapshots, docs describe the failure-containment contract, regression tests cover mutation leak prevention, and pm test plus test-all sweeps pass with 100 percent coverage."
  dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
    pm-b1w,parent,"2026-03-04T19:58:35.984Z",cursor-maintainer,null
  comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
    "2026-03-04T19:58:35.984Z",cursor-maintainer,"Why this exists: failed extension override and renderer handlers must not mutate fallback output state."
    "2026-03-04T19:58:45.520Z",cursor-maintainer,"Planned change-set: docs-first update for override and renderer failure-containment snapshot semantics, then loader runtime clone hardening plus mutation-leak regression tests."
    "2026-03-04T19:59:59.284Z",cursor-maintainer,"Docs-first update completed: PRD and README now require isolated result snapshots for command overrides and renderer overrides so failed extension handlers cannot leak mutation into fallback output."
    "2026-03-04T20:13:07.194Z",cursor-maintainer,"Implemented: loader runtime now runs command handlers, command overrides, and renderer overrides against structured-cloned context snapshots so extension-side mutation cannot leak into caller fallback state; added regression tests that mutate nested data before async/throw paths and verified no leakage. Evidence: pm test pm-8d71 --run --timeout 1800 --json passed totals 2/2 linked tests. pm test-all --status in_progress --timeout 1800 --json passed totals items=1 linked_tests=2 passed=2 failed=0 skipped=0. pm test-all --status closed --timeout 1800 --json passed totals items=56 linked_tests=184 passed=56 failed=0 skipped=128. Coverage remains 100 percent for lines/branches/functions/statements."
  notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
    "2026-03-04T19:58:35.984Z",cursor-maintainer,"Plan: docs first then loader runtime snapshot isolation then targeted tests and full regression sweeps."
  learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
    "2026-03-04T19:58:35.984Z",cursor-maintainer,"Hypothesis: cloning override and renderer context payloads closes remaining failure-containment leakage."
  files[4]{path,scope,note}:
    PRD.md,project,extension runtime failure containment contract
    README.md,project,document extension override and renderer snapshot behavior
    src/core/extensions/loader.ts,project,runtime snapshot isolation implementation
    tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts,project,regression coverage for mutation leak prevention
  tests[2]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds,note}:
    node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage,null,project,1800,coverage gate in sandbox
    node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts,null,project,900,targeted extension loader regression
  docs[3]{path,scope,note}:
    AGENTS.md,project,agent workflow contract
    PRD.md,project,governing spec
    README.md,project,public contract
body: Harden extension runtime failure containment by snapshotting override and renderer context payloads so failed handlers cannot leak mutations into fallback output.
